caption: I lived in Woodside & Jackson Heights Queens for almost a decade.  Indisputably the best Indian food in New York City.  I was bummed out about my lack of amazing Indian food choices when I moved back to Brooklyn.  They simply do not compare to Queens.  But this place is on point.  Consistently great.
Okay.
What a joke..

I ordered from this place last night and someone called me to tell me that if i want my 70 dollars order wich i already got charged 5 dollars delivery fee. I have to pay the delivery guy 10 more dollars cause apparently im to far. I refused to do so and wanted to cancel the order. The owner or manager kept calling and threatening me on why i canceled the order and that he was going to give me a free soda!!

I ordered samosa and baklava from this place omg its so horrible...samosa was so awful oil was dripping down from it and it was literally tasteless. I have never had such awful baklava in my life it was staled, so unhealthy, I wish I could give negative stars in review. Never ever gonna order from this place again
My food was yummy.great service.
I love the food here.
My food was Hot and fresh. Delivery was Fast.service Was great. I Will order food From this restaurant Again.
Very good place,i place the order first time chiken tikka masala,butter chiken and garlic naan.i recommended  every one order this.another opportunity  they open untill late Knight.

I order food from taz kabab king.all the food is delicious on time and delivery guy are very friendly serve door to door delivery its owesome restaurent is open till 3.45 thts easyer for me i gut.and they are service me since 2010.totaly..ok....ever..

Been going here for years, they’re just so reliably good. The Mulligatawny soup is amazing every single time, no other Indian spot does it the same way. My girlfriend said it’s some of the best Indian food she’s had in all NYC, I think she’s right.

$15 for a container of soup I would sell it for $2.. I will never order from here again..I only liked two things but they spice it up to much.. even my wife couldn’t eat all the meat with the rice cause to spicy😅
One of the best Indian restaurant I ever had, the food is so delicious. I’d love to order again, I really thank you guys for the food.

Taj Kabab one of the best Indian food in the town I never find great food like this restaurant I love them customer service and I have excellent food I try most of the time but I love Taj Kabab   Excellent testy foods
Best indin food in Brooklyn I enjoy 😉

Best Indian taj kebab  king restaurant in the city I live in Astoria  but I always order from them because they have a real Indian food  i enjoy I hope everybody will love this I really food enjoy  i almost every week 4 to 5 time I really appreciate  your service thank you  guys  i love  your  food ❤❤🇺🇸🌎

S P I C Y I Specifically requested not spicy at all. They told me yes no problem, while she was taking other orders on the phone. I can’t have any spicy food at all and I asked if it was possible. You lied to me and said yes, it’s fine. I can’t eat what I ordered. Thanks for not understanding customers requests.

I like to go with friends to this restaurant with my highest recommendations. I visit this restaurant often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The the cooking is fantastic and the team is generous and cooperative. Every time  we visit this place we have a gorgeous time.  I recommend this place with pleasure.
Very good Indian food! Saag paneer, Malawi kofta, tarka dal all great. Amazing samosa. Naan bread could use improvement. Thank you!

The food here is very tasty but my last experience with them was really off. There was a big mixup with my order where they only delivered the drinks but not the food. The delivery guy was VERY creepy and kept looking me up and down several times when I came to the door.

Great food! Don’t recommend the Aloo Partha just because it was under-cooked, anything bread/potato is pretty bad tbh but everything else is great! Long time customer chicken curry great and vegetable samosa
Always good food
We've been ordering from them exclusively ever since we first ordered a year ago. Definitely one of my Brooklyn favorites.

Waited for more than 50 minutes for the food (ordered through grubhub). Spent most of my lunch break on the phone and on chat with the restaurant and grubhub. The guy on the phone was telling me that they are having too many orders (?!). I told him that this is unacceptable answer and experience so he told me "go order from somewhere else, i have many other customers". SHOCKED! Even if their food is amazing, businesses should not take for granted their individuals and customers.

Food is always extremely late and cold. On deliveries ,they never answer the phone and it's impossible to know if it will come or not. they charge as fast as you order and then it's a coin toss.stay away
Good food, nice sized portions and very friendly service!  Prices are reasonable too.

This place is an unassuming gem. Best Indian food I’ve had in Brooklyn and I’ve been searching. Before you even order oftentimes you will receive a beautiful tomato lentil soup on the house and sometimes veggie pakora. The entrees I’ve had are incredible as well. Also open late night..you can’t beat it. My go-to for Indian food, very highly recommend!!!
Really enjoyed the food & the staff here is lovely!!

I think my relationship with Taj Kabab King has lasted longer than my relationship with any other institution in my life other than federal and state governments. Their food delicious and unpretentious. They have always been fast and reliable (even when I lived in Gramercy and LES and not, as I do now, a few blocks away). I consider them my benchmark for good food in New York.
Great food, amazing value. Everything I ate was delicious.

Butter Chicken it is, is my favorite Indian dish, I usually get it from any Indian restaurant I visit. This one I can say is excellent in taste as to other places. I came here with a few friends for a night and we all loved it. It is not my average 10.00 lunch though. It was $25.00 for the Butter Chicken with 3 garlic naans, enough for 2 people.  I really don't know of many different Indian dishes, however, I can always get it right with Butter Chicken.

Had an awesome dinner platter consisting of a great thick piece of salmon, nice appetizers, a real spicy soup (not too spicy hot) and a small side called crab curry. My friend had a regular lamb lunch that was smallish but sufficient. All delish. Nice service.

My favorite Indian place for eat-in and take-out. The service at the restaurant is fantastic and included complimentary appetizers. Takeout is always timely, hot, exactly what I ordered and most importantly, delicious. When moving apartments, I made sure I was still in the Taj Kabab King delivery radius.
This place is really good but we ordered Chana Shag and it was 99.9% chickpea! Was so disappointing bcuz we love this dish and there was no spinach.

Sub par lunch delivery. No silverware. Soup was just sauce base. entree was same sauce with three bite-size pieces of lamb and maybe potato. Naan was hot. Pakoras fresh. So maybe skip their delivery lunch. They obviously cannot provide meat/app/soup/bread/rice at $11 and meet the customer’s expectation.
The best and tastiest Indian cuisine period!
My absolute neighborhood favorite!
Great food
Reliable local spot
Awesome spot, if you’re looking for the best Lassi’s, search no more! Everything has great taste and the staff is super friendly!
I had a wonderful experience at this restaurant. We enjoyed the great environment and the menu. The staff members are super affable. I am glad we ultimately managed to visit this restaurant.

Indian eats, open until 2:45 am, pretty straightforward! We go late & the service is always fast & extra accommodating (although I'm sure it helps my wife is Nepali). They have plenty of vegetarian & vegan options, favorites being the Muligatawny Soup, Mushroom Bhaji with Garlic Naan. Delivery is free until late as well!
So, so good! Chicken Tikka Masala and Sag Aloo both delicious.
Liked the look was good clean and staff nice
Great food, inexpensive nice staff
Oll Time good food
All I can say is this place is terrible!

The restaurant was clean and service was really fast. I got my lunch special really quick. The lamb samosa was a bit dry and you could tell it was microwaved. The chutneys were watery. However, the Vindaloo I got was worth.
DO NOT ORDER!!! THEY ARE RUDE!!!
Amazing food and service!

Delicious ! We 3 french girls came to eat at this indian restaurant and we were so well served, really taken care of. So much food for a very reasonable price, we had to take doggy bags as we didn’t even eat half ! They were adorable, it was very fast-served, the restaurant is small but very typical indian so quite cute !  Very surprised to see some negative comments, I suggest eating at the restaurant itself rather than complaining about delivery !  Thank you for your adorable service ⭐️
Very good food and service. Would recommend to anyone.
I can’t believe that they put  all the order for delivery in the floor in the kitchen that’s very weird

Good service and great value for the price. It some of the dishes I have had were a bit over cooked but not enough that I couldn’t enjoy it. Overall I would recommend, just wouldn’t take my parents here if they were visiting
Amazing!!! very fast delivery and the food was great. Glad we found a local India spot!
I ordered assorted Indian hors d’oeuver For take out . It’s amazing it’s definitely a restaurant I would come back

The manager of Taj Kabab King actively encourages his drivers to illegally park in the protected bike lane in front of the restaurant, putting the lives of hundreds of cyclists at risk every day. Profits are not more important than safety.
Very nice customer service. The food is very delicious, very flavorful and the manager really cares about the customers. Will keep coming back here for the house special briyani and cheese naan.
Ordered for saag paneer and two naan. I paid $22.00 but it doesn't worth. Food quality is very low.
I was so disappointed when I order lentils soup and I got tomato soup. I asked if it was a mistake and they told me it is lentil soup. The salmon wan not well cook. It was raw from inside.
Very good food

So much deliciousness for such a good price. Great place to bring friends who can't decide. With so many options everyone can be fulfilled. Plus the costumer service was to notch. Vegan and vegetarian options!!!
Great food. When you eat in, you get a ton of food and excellent service.
Not bad. It’s a no frills standard Indian with nothing particularly outstanding about it.  I am torn between rounding up or down because it probably deserves a 3.5 stars.
The food wasn’t ready after I ordered 30 minutes prior to arriving. I think they threw it together really fast and it tasted like nothing. My garlic naan had NO garlic or seasoning. Big bummer.
Great food and excellent lunch deal.
Good food at great little cozy place. Friendly staff and good service. Love the samosas!! I bring home a dozen or so every time I visit so I can have them all week long.

Super disappointing.  I ordered a lentil soup (mulligatawny soup really) and I got a tomato soup.  I called regarding the mistake.  I was told that was the lentil soup.  It was not.  He said they mix tomato with it.  It was like tomato paste.  The Indian restaurant on Havemeyer makes a great lentil soup.  I wanted to try a different restaurant and would not order from here again. No taste.  The curry was okay and the Rasmali were eatable but wouldn’t order there again.
food is really good. Employee and owner Afsar is really really friendly. I will recommend taj kabab king. Really delicious. Thx for everything taj kabab king. Love this restaurant
How is this rated so high? I’ll get to it the shrimp was not cleaned, the flavor none, there were 4 pieces of shrimp and sauce for $12, rice as not saffron, the naan a joke. Would like my money back.
I’ve eaten in many Indian restaurant in the neighborhood, this place is THE BEST!!!
Great food, ordered from them multiple times excellent every time

Been eating here since I was 13 I'm 20 now I'm in love with this place always have always will be it is truly blessed authentic and the vibe is just so comforting especially when eating it makes you feel like you're in india🙏🏾 The people here are truly the gods in human skin feeding our blasphemous American asses real food for once, should eat here it's the culture 🖤 Who ever is writing bad reviews about this place is trying too take out competition they're clearly mad business owners trying too steal the greatness from this shop because their restaurants suck. Stop being demonic everyone should eat here it's truly lovely
One of the worst place not an Indian cuisine fooling people actually it's a Bangladeshi restaurant using Indian dishes name please don't get fooled

I used to dig this place for years both dine in & take out but our last experience was super disappointing. Acknowledging that most of their business is take out, when you eat in you have to be prepared to experience a bit of foot traffic, delivery guys walking in and out quite frequently. However on Sunday, 6 delivery guys where standing around in the back of the restaurant (place is small) by the kitchen entrance/restrooms, talking loudly and constantly walking back and forth between smoking cigarettes outside and loudly talking inside/on phone. It felt like a train station and we where actually the only customers in there at that point.  This wasn't by far the worst of it. Our server had a cold and kept pulling up snot, coughing and picking his nose. I was so disgusted by him constantly snorting his snot back up his nose (instead of simply using a tissue), we requested boxes to take our food to go and left to finish our dinner at home. Needless to say I have first symptoms of a cold today with a cough and sore throat. This is so gross and simplest service industry rule number one, DON NOT COME TO WORK WHEN YOU ARE SICK, you spread is to dozens of people through food handling!  Extra bummer: the rice was undercooked (absolute first for me in an indian restaurant). Another last bummer, my husband is allergic to almonds and we had slices almonds sprinkled over both our dishes, after we intentionally ordered none of the sauces that contain almonds. Unfortunately will never be back. :/

Ordered through grubhub. The food came on time and was hot but the food wasn't good at alllllll. Nothing personal against the restaurant but just giving an honest review. The tomato soup was the worst I've ever seen or tasted from texture to taste. It seemed like they mix canned tomato puree with water and lots of oil. Other items didn't taste good as well and food had a lot of color in it (not turmeric, being Indian I know what turmeric looks like). I had colour on my hands after eating which wouldn't go away even from multiple washings.
Worth the occasional wait. Best Indian food I've had in New York. The owner is caring and observant. I'm happy to be living in the neighborhood. So much papdum
I've only ordered on seamless, but I hope to go in person soon. The food is amazing.

very surprising, just read the reviews. the last two reviews seems written intentionally to defame the customer service as well as restaurant . I visit the place frequently. As a Bangali customer they take good care, behave very well even they make the dish special for me. They are very caring for all the customer, this is the reason they have been running the business successfully since 2010.if those reviews were true, they had to close the restaurant right after they started. I would suggest customers that do visit the place,  you will find the best customer service

Just now had dinner. Worst customer service ever . The serve was very rude. I asked for naan and the server said that this is not the place. SARVER ASFER WAS A VERY RUDE.. its better to avoid this place.
Mr. Asfer is the owner of the place. Very stupid and rude guy. Worst Indian food quality.. guys plz avoid the place ...
Great food for a very good price! We had the lunch special which comes with soup and starter. The food was excellent and we really enjoyed it!

Great take out. Very quick and the portions are large.
Excellent food, spices are to die for. If you love Indian food or even like it you will fall in love w their food. The salmon is huge & done right.
Service is really bad.
The wine selection was OK; they only serve two kinds of beer - Kingfisher in a regular-sized bottle and (I believe) Taj Mahal in a large bottle. Next time I will ask if we can bring… read more
We went there for Christmas eve !! Good food and nice service (they served us an extra starters : soup and potatoes fritters)
Excellent service. Great food at a good price
Good food.
Not great,  bad service and mediocre food

Dry chicken burnt outside, inside like leather. The chicken was tiny and container full of raw vegetables. The unpeeled raw carrot was sincerely the highlight. I didn't need rice with bone dry chicken but got it anyway. Google needs zero stars, 1 is too high.

Excellent service. Great food at a good price. Chill atmosphere. Sometimes they throw in a soup or app on the house.

The food is good, but my order was completely wrong. And "iced tea" apparently means canned high fructose corn syrup lemon Fuze. Was craving Rasmalai late at night badly, was given the honey balls instead ☹️
Solid Indian with all the classics, yummy stuff.
The food is decent, but on a Sunday night we ordered dinner at 8:30 and didn't get our food until 10:15 and it was cold. This is some serious BS won't be ordering from them again.
My server was monzu he was very kind and knowledgable. They even gave me some free apps since the lunch shift was slow that day. Everything was delicious and reasonably priced.

I went here for the first time the other day on a friend's recommendation.  Delicious food - I don't think I've ever had Indian food that I didn't like, but this was far better than most. Very attentive, kind, and fast service. Highly recommend.  The spicy dishes are not for the faint of heart
We love Taj Kabab . . . great food and service.  Monzu is especially friendly and helpful.  I highly recommend!!!!
This place is great-- the food is phenomenal, the portions are good sized and not too pricey, and the service is on point (Monzu is the man)!

I'm totally blown away by the rave reviews this place has on Yelp, Google, and Seamless. I ordered from Seamless, and since their terrible user interface won't let me rate the restaurant on their site, I'm posting here.  Ordered some of the basics, Tikka Masala, Curry, Kathi roll, naan. Aside from the naan everything else was awful. Granted, I ordered late at night, but still the meal was basically inedible, and expensive. The Tikka and Curry sauces were basically just greasy paste, and the kathi roll was literally just raw tomato and lettuce wrapped in fried naan. Even the rice was overcooked.  I never post Google reviews, but this was garbage and I'm pissed that Seamless won't let me rate it there, so here we are. Again, can't understand why this restaurant is so highly rated. Complete waste of money, don't even bother.

I've become a regular at Taj Kabab King. It's a great Indian cuisine and both lunch and dinner specials for the quantity of food and price are unbeatable! You get a soup, 2 appetizers, one delicious warm Naan bread, one tea', and 2 main courses for $14.95. Probably the butter chicken is one of their best and our favorite dish!  All the waiters are all really friendly. The last waiter we had, named "Monzu", was so great that we couldn't ignore to leave a great review about him. Probably one of the most genuine nice waiters we've had in a long time. He made us change some stuff we wanted different on our dinner special and even offered us an extra soup and one extra appetizer. If you like Indian food, are hungry and want to spend little but still eat great food, go here!
Had a great meal here last night! Monju was our waiter, and couldn't have been more friendly. Food was top notch and the atmosphere was nice.
Expectacular food!!! Amazing ambient and service. Monzu, supero fantástico waiter! And affordable!!!
Munzu was a-munzing! Would def recommend
(Translated by Google) Meh  (Original) Meh
Best Indian food in this area. The service is super gentle and professional and the food is great. It's Williamsburg staple

Very delicious food and friendly staff. The Sag Paneer and Spicy vegetable soup are some of the best I've had, and it was also very nice of the staff to give us additional appetizers on the house out of generosity. I highly recommend Taj Kabab King!

After 8 years of coming to Grand st I cannot believe I have not had Indian food from here. What was I thinking. Service was amazing. Yes there was a wait and I called ahead. Guys were super nice and offered me a free soda while waited. Food was delicious by the way. Will definitely go back soon.

This place is the best. We order from here ALL the time on seamless and just went into the restaurant for the first time today. The service was excellent! Our waiter Monju was so nice and even gave us an app and soup on the house. The food was Delicious as always.
Monju was very friendly and I did very much enjoy the Chicken Bindaloo. Way better than all the fast food here and for a reasonable price.

We had a really good time here with my friends and I couldn't recommand it more. Monju was really kind with us and he was the perfect host. Great quality food and good quantity for the price. Go and try it!
Wonderful place with awesome food and Nice peuple ! Thank you Monju for the perfect welcoming
Monzu is great!  And the food at lunch is very good too.
We normally get delivery but the eat-in service is really above and beyond great. Monju is awesome :)
Really excellent service and friendly staff ! I really liked my Binda Aloo! Would definitely recommend. Great dining experience

Came in for the Chicken Tikka lunch special for $10. The Nan bread was absolutely fluffy and full of goodness - a perfect compliment to the soup that you're given to enjoy in it's full nan-ny goodness. The vegetable samosa (and meat samosa too) is big and very flavorful that also goes greatly with the soup. The sauces that come with the meal (one is a sliced red pepper, another is a green sauce and another brown) are very nice ways to bring out the taste. The chicken was very nicely cut and full of masala goodness. Absolutely delicious. The rice portion was huge and had some good qualities to it - not too watery, not too hard.. very delicate. Service is fast and you are consistently on by the friendly staff. The decor is beautiful and reminds you of India. Our waiter, Monju, was very charismatic and social and really made the trip to the restaurant extremely pleasant. Highly recommended.

Best Indian/Bangladeshi restaurant in Williamsburg! Food is delicious, the place is quiet, very clean, they use tablecloths and traditional tableware, and the music selection is really relaxing. Ask Monju, the nice and friendly manager, to recommend their best courses — he'll make you happy! My favorite: Vegetarian Menu... just D E L I C I O U S !

Great place and great service (our waiter was Monju). We got the dinner special and we loved it, we were so full with good food that we ended up each with a left over to take home. Recommended to all Indian food lovers, especially for the great price.
The food is very delicious. A nice little restaurant.monzu is a good server.

An amazing experience coming into this restaurant. Monzu and our server were beyond attentive and funny! We were so full and happy when we left after having the #1 and #2 dinner special. we split it between the three of us and felt like Queens **in brooklyn. We'd definitely come back for another night out. Perfect food and service.
Y The food is excellent and very reasonable. You must go.

I absolutely love this place! The food and service are fantastic and byob makes it by far the most affordable sit down restaurant in Williamsburg.  My personal favorite is the seafood dinner special. Shrimp or crab curry and the best tandoori salmon I've ever had with soup and appetizers included.  Ask for Monzu, he will take amazing care of you!

This is the best Indian food we've had in NYC since moving from London in 2012 - so happy we found this place! Its super reasonable and every dish we had was delicious - they also do brown rice which is great. Our server Monju was so so friendly too, and gave us free extras - a lentil soup + veg pakora - while we waited for our food. We will come back often!

Food was absolutely delicious! We had the chicken curry and shrimp curry lunch specials, lot of food for a very reasonable price. Server (Monju) is very friendly and kind. Great Customer Service and pleasant atmosphere...would definitely return and tell my friends and family about Taj Kabab King, must try!!

This is the tastiest, most authentic, most comprehensive snapshot of Indian cuisine in Brooklyn. Monzu and the rest of the staff delight being attentive to their guests, many of whom are recognized and welcomed with a hearty greeting. Becoming a regular here is the smartest thing you can do if you love Indian food like I do.
Fantastic curry. Really tasty spiced tea. Monzu, our waiter, was incredibly kind and helpful 😄
Awesome food.  Had a server named Monju who suggested a dish that wasn't on the menu and my girlfriend loved it.  Definitely recommend.

Best Indian spot in Brooklyn.  Great staff headed by Monzu is always comping me hor dourves and side dishes till I can hardly walk out. Love this place I highly recommend to anyone interested in great food and service.

Very good Indian food and great service.  We were served by Nadheem and he was very cheerful and took every detail in attention.  I would strongly recommend this place and service ... Kudos Nadheem !!!
I love this place. Thank you for the excellent service!!!!  Best food.
Taj Kebab King is our go-to spot for Indian food. Delicious and with really, really generous servings. Friendly service as well.

I have only ever ordered delivery, but it's cheap and great. As a Pakistani-American, I am picky about my Indian restaurants, but this place is consistently great. I usually get the veggie dinner special, which comes with way too much food for one person. I also love that the saag paneer and chicken tikka masala isn't soupy, but thick. Really fast at delivery too!
almost impossible to finish your dishes, for $15 and that's SO good

Actually called "Taj Kabab King"  I live close by and eat here or order from here all the time. I love it. Pretty much get some on a weekly basis at this point because I like it so much.  Must order:  Samosa - Coconut is good, Lamb and Veggie are really good. Salmon Taj Kahari - my favorite thing on the menu.  There are a ton of great vegetarian entrees. I've had 3 or 4 different ones and really loved each of them.
